    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-25T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-25T08:00:00-05:00" n="203"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d203">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">103.917/5085: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Warren</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ciudad Trujillo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-25T08:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 25, 1943—8 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 26—5 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–611. For Foreign Economic Administration.<note n="83" xml:id="d203fn83">The
                        Office of Economic Warfare, formerly the Board of Economic Warfare, was
                        consolidated into the Foreign Economic Administration, September 25,
                        1943.</note> As requested by Department’s circular airgram of November 13,
                        1943<note n="84" xml:id="d203fn84">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_131">p. 131</ref>.</note> the
                    Embassy <pb facs="0216" n="204" xml:id="pg_204"/> reports that the additional
                    simplifications of export controls referred to in the above airgram have been
                    communicated to the Dominican Import-Export Control Committee and that the
                    Committee has expressed its acceptance of and complete agreement with such
                    proposals.</p>
                <p>In accordance with the Department’s instructions, the revised procedure will
                    become effective in the Dominican Republic on January 1, 1944.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Warren</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
